                <head>409. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Commander in Chief, Pacific, Admiral <persName corresp="#p_RVAHD1">Herbert
                        Riley</persName>, and his Assistant Political Adviser, <persName
                        corresp="#p_CTJ1">Thomas Corcoran</persName>, visited Vientiane September
                    24–26. They held discussions with the members of the Country Team and with all
                    the political officers in the Embassy. <persName corresp="#p_RVAHD1"
                        >Riley</persName>’s account of the visit is in <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1"
                        >CINCPAC</gloss> telegram 5849 to the Joint Chiefs of Staff, September 29.
                    (Department of State, EA Files: Lot 68 D 77, Laos 1960, Part I) <persName
                        corresp="#p_CTJ1">Corcoran</persName> wrote his own impressions of the trip
                    in a memorandum to Sterling Cottrell, <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1"
                        >CINCPAC</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_POLAD1">POLAD</gloss>, September 30. (Washington National
                    Records Center, <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_ISA1"
                        >ISA</gloss> Files: FRC 64 A 2170, 092 Asia) Cottrell sent a letter to
                        <persName corresp="#p_PJG1">Parsons</persName> on October 1 explaining his
                    view of the visit and providing <persName corresp="#p_PJG1">Parsons</persName> a
                    copy of <persName corresp="#p_CTJ1">Corcoran</persName>’s memorandum.
                    (Department of State, <gloss target="#t_FESEA1">FE/SEA</gloss> (Laos) Files: Lot
                    65 D 169, 350 Pol Affairs, 10/60 Laos)</p>
                <p>All these documents are included in <ref target="frus1958-60v15-16mSupp1">the
                        microfiche supplement</ref>.</p>
            </div>
